Package: bbeaR
Type: Package
Title: EbbeaR: an R package and framework for epitope-specific antibody profiling
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Maria Suprun, Randall J. Ellis, Hugh A. Sampson, Mayte Suárez-Fariñas
Date: October 9, 2020
Maintainer: Maria Suprun <maria.suprun@icahn.mssm.edu>
Depends: MASS, ggplot2, plyr, Biobase, igraph, reshape2, stringr, fitdistrplus
Description: bbeaR is an open-source R package that provides a framework to import, process and normalize .csv data files exported from the Luminex reader, evaluate various quality control metrics, analyze and visualize the differential epitope-binding antibodies, and map epitope amino acid sequences to their respective primary protein structures. bbeaR enables streamlined and reproducible analysis of epitope-specific antibody profiles.       
License: N/A
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
